1. requirement analysis
collect information from stakeholders using techiniquires such as interviews and observation
2.requirement categorization
.functional requirements -what the system must do
.non-functional requirements-quality attributes
.business requirement-high level goals
.user requirement- what useers expect
3. requiremet analysis
checks feasability, consistency and completeness.using models such as use case daigrams and progress flow daigrams.
4.requirement documentation
create a software requirement specifications document.srs includes such as introduction and scope , functional requireemnts etc
5.requirenent valuidatuion
confirm with stakeholders that requirements are correct,complete, consistent and testable.
6. re  quirement mangement
requirements may change ,track update and update them.
